Milestone Audit - July 11, 2026

This document evaluates our progress against the technical milestones set on 2026-07-09 as we prepare to transition into Phase 2 of the AI Job Agent platform.

Milestone 1: Implement Candidate Profile Fingerprints

Goal: Avoid unnecessary re-evaluations when candidate data has not changed.
Status: 🟡 PARTIALLY ACHIEVED (Backend Active, n8n Integration Pending)

What Is Done:

The Math & Crypto: Created generate_profile_fingerprint in scripts/hashing_utils.py which computes:


$$\text{Fingerprint} = \text{SHA256}(\text{Sorted Skills} \mathbin{\Vert} \text{Cleaned Experience} \mathbin{\Vert} \text{Sorted Preferred Roles})$$

The Database Schema: Added profile_fingerprint to the candidates table and candidate_snapshot_fingerprint to the evaluations table.

The Ingestion Check: Updated scripts/save_candidate.py. When a candidate resume is uploaded, it generates this hash. If the database finds a matching email with the same hash, it skips the write entirely, preventing redundant database updates.

What Is Missing (The "Last Mile"):

n8n Payloads: The n8n workflow currently retrieves candidate data but does not pass the candidate's profile_fingerprint along to /save-evaluation in its final POST request.

API Validation: api.py and its Pydantic EvaluationRequest model do not yet expect or validate this fingerprint.

Milestone 2: Extend Fingerprinting to Job Descriptions

Goal: Enable selective re-evaluation when job requirements change.
Status: 🟡 PARTIALLY ACHIEVED (Basic Uniqueness Locked, Semantic Requirements Pending)

What Is Done:

Unique Identification: Added job_fingerprint to the jobs database schema.

Scraper Guard: Built calculate_job_fingerprint(title, company, location) in seed_database.py. This ensures we do not import duplicate jobs from external scraper engines.

What Is Missing (The "Last Mile"):

Semantic Requirements Tracking: The hash is currently generated using only title + company + location to prevent duplicate listings. To detect when a recruiter changes the actual requirements of an active job, we must expand the hash:


$$\text{Fingerprint}_{\text{job}} = \text{SHA256}(\text{Title} \mathbin{\Vert} \text{Company} \mathbin{\Vert} \text{Requirements JSON})$$

Delta Matching Trigger: We have not yet written the endpoint or DB trigger to locate historical evaluations matching a changed job fingerprint and flag them for re-evaluation.

Milestone 3: Introduce Evaluation Versioning

Goal: Support reproducible AI assessments across future model and prompt updates.
Status: 🔴 PENDING (Conceptualized in ADR, Not Coded)

What Is Done:

Architectural Blueprint: Outlined the requirements in docs/adr_re_evaluation_strategy.md. We designed the schemas to support reproducible evaluations.

What Is Missing:

Database Updates: We need to add columns to the evaluations table:

model_version (e.g., "qwen2.5:7b")

prompt_version (e.g., "v1.0")

Tracking Logic: We need to pass these values dynamically from our n8n pipeline. If you update your prompt in n8n, the system should recognize the version mismatch and execute a re-evaluation despite candidate/job fingerprints matching.

Immediate Next Steps to Complete Milestones

To close out these milestones completely before shifting to the scraper, we should:

Update api.py's EvaluationRequest model to accept candidate_snapshot_fingerprint and job_fingerprint.

Update the n8n Build Prompt and POST Save Evaluation nodes to pass these fingerprints.

Hardcode model and prompt version tracking into the n8n execution variables.

